{"id": "EUVD-2022-55272", "enisaUuid": "80014e72-71cf-3e61-8e6e-3bdc38a6a894", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nloop: Check for overflow while configuring loop\n\nThe userspace can configure a loop using an ioctl call, wherein\na configuration of type loop_config is passed (see lo_ioctl()'s\ncase on line 1550 of drivers/block/loop.c). This proceeds to call\nloop_configure() which in turn calls loop_set_status_from_info()\n(see line 1050 of loop.c), passing &config->info which is of type\nloop_info64*. This function then sets the appropriate values, like\nthe offset.\n\nloop_device has lo_offset of type loff_t (see line 52 of loop.c),\nwhich is typdef-chained to long long, whereas loop_info64 has\nlo_offset of type __u64 (see line 56 of include/uapi/linux/loop.h).\n\nThe function directly copies offset from info to the device as\nfollows (See line 980 of loop.c):\n\tlo->lo_offset = info->lo_offset;\n\nThis results in an overflow, which triggers a warning in iomap_iter()\ndue to a call to iomap_iter_done() which has:\n\tWARN_ON_ONCE(iter->iomap.offset > iter->pos);\n\nThus, check for negative value during loop_set_status_from_info().\n\nBug report: https://syzkaller.appspot.com/bug?id=c620fe14aac810396d3c3edc9ad73848bf69a29e", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T11:00:53", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-23T13:26:22", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/18e28817cb516b39de6281f6db9b0618b2cc7b42", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/adf0112d9b8acb03485624220b4934f69bf13369", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a217715338fd48f72114725aa7a40e484a781ca7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b40877b8562c5720d0a7fce20729f56b75a3dede", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6858933131d0dadac071c4d33335a9ea4b8e76cf", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0455bef69028c65065f16bb04635591b2374249b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9be7fa7ead18a48940df7b59d993bbc8b9055c15", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c490a0b5a4f36da3918181a8acdc6991d967c5f3", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49993"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49993"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0cc09f1a-8cd7-3037-828d-7a603b5f5077", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.6"}, {"id": "24025592-fd8b-363f-a2da-e60f3e44c97e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <adf0112d9b8acb03485624220b4934f69bf13369"}, {"id": "2a4b1d38-246f-3f65-81e8-b5ed4251ccc5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.64"}, {"id": "2d20976e-caa2-37f4-91d0-4eb46e39885e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <0455bef69028c65065f16bb04635591b2374249b"}, {"id": "2e53ddfe-9f55-3a78-875b-dabeb8ac2e1b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <6858933131d0dadac071c4d33335a9ea4b8e76cf"}, {"id": "400a8cf0-e85e-39d9-93ba-845f66bc7b44", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2.6.12"}, {"id": "4b61b295-2781-3859-9eb1-ef148007b57c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "500c075d-c3a5-3d59-b14b-fbf994e69919", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.19.312"}, {"id": "66a8fc21-fb91-32f1-b34f-b93eba1f3cac", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <b40877b8562c5720d0a7fce20729f56b75a3dede"}, {"id": "92ccdb74-6cc7-305b-9cd1-08a9356f89b7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.140"}, {"id": "9a2b2816-7dfc-34ad-ba00-f2a6b286b8c7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.14.292"}, {"id": "9d0c95fd-b680-34c5-b475-78db8a0356d3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.9.327"}, {"id": "ad3fdf12-b547-3e05-9dc5-a583d1172619", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <18e28817cb516b39de6281f6db9b0618b2cc7b42"}, {"id": "afe4ce29-7765-